TableView.name: LOCATION_V2
TableView.commentInRDBMS: Defines the physical branches of the library.
TableView.userDefinedSQL: CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW LOCATION_V2 AS SELECT INSTBIT,LOCNUMBER,LOCCODE,LOCNAME,RENEWALSALLOWED,DOESNOTCIRCULATEFLAG,ALLOWRECALL, ALLOWHOLDS,FINEGRACEPERIOD,FINELIMIT,FINERATE,FINEASSESSMENTTYPE,OVERRIDENOFINE, REQUESTFINEGRACEPERIOD,REQUESTFINELIMIT,REQUESTFINERATE,REQUESTFINEASSESSMENTTYPE, CHARGELOANPERIOD,RENEWLOANPERIOD,RECALLLOANPERIOD,REQUESTCHARGELOANPERIOD, REQUESTRENEWLOANPERIOD,REQUESTRECALLLOANPERIOD,CHARGELIMIT,RENEWALLIMIT,PROCESSINGFEE, LOSTBOOKCHARGE,SPECIALFEE,MAGNETICMEDIA,NOTICEDAYS_0,SENDNOTICE,NOTICEFEES_0, NOTICEFEES_1,NOTICEFEES_2,NOTICEFEES_3,NOTICEFEES_4,NOTICEFEES_5,LOSTNOTICEDAYS_0, LOSTNOTICEDAYS_1,LOSTNOTICEDAYS_2,SENDLOSTNOTICE,LOSTNOTICEFEES_0,LOSTNOTICEFEES_1, LOSTNOTICEFEES_2,RECALLNOTICEDAYS_0,RECALLNOTICEDAYS_1,RECALLNOTICEDAYS_2, RECALLNOTICEDAYS_3,RECALLNOTICEDAYS_4,RECALLNOTICEDAYS_5,SENDRECALLNOTICE, RECALLNOTICEFEES_0,RECALLNOTICEFEES_1,RECALLNOTICEFEES_2,RECALLNOTICEFEES_3, RECALLNOTICEFEES_4,RECALLNOTICEFEES_5,FINESNOTICEDAYS_0,FINESNOTICEDAYS_1, FINESNOTICEDAYS_2,SENDFINENOTICE,FINESNOTICEFEES_0,HOLDNOTICEFEE,FINESNOTICEFEES_1, FINESNOTICEFEES_2,NOTICEDAYS_1,NOTICEDAYS_2,NOTICEDAYS_3,NOTICEDAYS_4,NOTICEDAYS_5, INTELLECTUAL_LEVEL,CIRCULATION_LEVEL,ALLOWFLOATINGCOLLECTION FROM CXDAT.LOCATION

viewElement.name: INSTBIT
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Numeric institution code

viewElement.name: LOCNUMBER
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Unique number assigned to the location

viewElement.name: LOCCODE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Up-to-6-character code assigned to a location within a branch(es)

viewElement.name: LOCNAME
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Name of the location

viewElement.name: RENEWALSALLOWED
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Determines whether items with this location code are eligible for renewal

viewElement.name: DOESNOTCIRCULATEFLAG
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether items from this location may be checked out

viewElement.name: ALLOWRECALL
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether items with this specific parameter value may be recalled

viewElement.name: ALLOWHOLDS
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Indicates whether items with this specific parameter value may fill holds

viewElement.name: FINEGRACEPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of days an item can be returned overdue without generating a fine

viewElement.name: FINELIMIT
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Maximum fine that is calculated for the return of overdue or lost items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: FINERATE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Daily rate of fine that is calculated for the return of overdue or lost items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: FINEASSESSMENTTYPE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Assessment type for fines (D for Daily)

viewElement.name: OVERRIDENOFINE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Standard override no fine

viewElement.name: REQUESTFINEGRACEPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of days a recalled item can be returned overdue without generating a fine

viewElement.name: REQUESTFINELIMIT
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Maximum fine that is calculated for the return of overdue or lost and recalled items with this speciric parameter value

viewElement.name: REQUESTFINERATE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Daily rate of fine that is calculated for the return of overdue or lost and recalled items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: REQUESTFINEASSESSMENTTYPE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Assessment type for fines on hold or recalled (D for Daily)

viewElement.name: CHARGELOANPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of days used to calculate a due date for items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: RENEWLOANPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of days used to calculate a renewal due date for items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: RECALLLOANPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of days used to calculate the shortened due date for recalled items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: REQUESTCHARGELOANPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Request charge loan period

viewElement.name: REQUESTRENEWLOANPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Request renew loan period

viewElement.name: REQUESTRECALLLOANPERIOD
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Request recall loan period

viewElement.name: CHARGELIMIT
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of items with this specific parameter value that a patron may have checked out at any given time

viewElement.name: RENEWALLIMIT
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Number of times the patron may renew items with this specific parameter value

viewElement.name: PROCESSINGFEE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Processing fee associated with lost items from this branch.

viewElement.name: LOSTBOOKCHARGE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Lost book charge for items from this branch. If data is not entered here, the default amount set at the institution level is used.

viewElement.name: SPECIALFEE
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Special fee assessed for an item checked out from this location

viewElement.name: MAGNETICMEDIA
viewElement.commentInRDBMS: Indicates that items with this specific parameter value should not be de-sensitized by the self-check machine
